    <section class="page-intro">
        <p>
            Cleveland, situated on the southern shore of Lake Erie, is a city with a rich industrial history and
            cultural heritage.
            Incorporated in 1836, Cleveland has a population of over 370,000.
            The city is known for its significant contributions to manufacturing, healthcare, and finance.
            Cleveland boasts a thriving arts and cultural scene, with landmarks such as the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame,
            the Cleveland Museum of Art, and Playhouse Square.
            Sports enthusiasts can enjoy major league teams like the Cleveland Browns, Cleveland Cavaliers, and
            Cleveland Guardians.
            With its beautiful lakefront, diverse neighborhoods, and robust economic opportunities, Cleveland is a
            vibrant place to call home.
        </p>
    </section>

